standardized_response.result: Barack Hussein Obama, an American politician, served as the 44th president of the United States from 2009 to 2017. A Democrat, Obama was the first African-American U.S. president. He was also a U.S. senator from Illinois from 2005 to 2008, and an Illinois state senator from 1997 to 2004.
